title: Owasco Airport
text:
Owasco Airport is a privately owned, public use <a href="airport">airport</a> located three <a href="nautical%20mile">nautical mile</a>s (6 <a href="kilometre">km</a>) northwest of the <a href="central%20business%20district">central business district</a> of <a href="Moravia%20%28village%29%2C%20New%20York">Moravia</a>, a village in the <a href="Moravia%20%28town%29%2C%20New%20York">Town of Moravia</a>, <a href="Cayuga%20County%2C%20New%20York">Cayuga County</a>, <a href="New%20York%20%28state%29">New York</a>, <a href="United%20States">United States</a>.
It was formerly a private use airport with the FAA identifier NY92.
Facilities.
Owasco Airport covers an area of 52 <a href="acre">acre</a>s (21 <a href="hectare">ha</a>) at an <a href="elevation">elevation</a> of 1,378 feet (420 m) above <a href="mean%20sea%20level">mean sea level</a>. It has one <a href="runway">runway</a> designated 11/29 with a <a href="grass">turf</a> surface measuring 2,300 by 50 feet (701 x 15 m).
